<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11020</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr><route>erct-001K.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11021</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11022</anchor>  <addr>erct-003Q</addr><route>erct-003Q.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › closure properties</title>  <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11023</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr><route>erct-001K.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11024</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11025</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr><route>erct-001L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11026</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003X</addr><route>erct-003X.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> identification types</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003X.agda" type="external">erct-003X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11027</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The centre of contraction of <tex>x=y</tex> is given by our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>; the contracting identifications are obtained from the same assumption via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11028</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003Y</addr><route>erct-003Y.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> identification types</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11029</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base case for <tex>n=-2</tex> is given by <ref addr="erct-003X" href="erct-003X.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, and the other cases are trivial.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11030</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr><route>erct-002T.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11031</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases given by <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11032</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002U</addr><route>erct-002U.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002U.agda" type="external">erct-002U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11033</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Immediate by identification induction.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11034</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002V</addr><route>erct-002V.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> for all <tex>n</tex></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002V.agda" type="external">erct-002V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> for all <tex>n</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11035</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>: when <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall that the <link href="erct-002U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002U" title="The identity map is contractible">identity map is contractible</link>, and in the inductive step we apply the <link href="erct-002T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002T" title="Truncation is upward closed">upward closure of <tex>n</tex>-truncation</link> to each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11036</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr><route>erct-0026.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11037</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11038</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr><route>erct-0027.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11039</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  B  \to  A</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  A \to  B</tex>; if <tex>a_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex> is given by <tex>ra_0</tex>. For the rest, we use <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11040</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003S</addr><route>erct-003S.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> type is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11041</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base cases for <tex>n=-2</tex> and <tex>n=-1</tex> are given by <ref addr="erct-002V" href="erct-002V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> exhibits <tex>B</tex> as a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and that for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=_Ay</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> to show that for all <tex>u,v:B</tex> the identification type <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is likewise <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is (by <ref addr="erct-003U" href="erct-003U.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>) a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>su=_Asv</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11042</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr><route>erct-001H.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractible type</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11043</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr><route>erct-001I.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11044</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0048</addr><route>erct-0048.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">Embeddings</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0048.agda" type="external">erct-0048.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11045</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-0048</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must check that for every <tex>b:B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> at <tex>b</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Fixing <tex>u_0,u_1: \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, b</tex> we must check that <tex>u_0=u_1</tex>. We let <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_0,p_0 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_0</tex> and <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_1,p_1 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_1</tex> so that we have <tex>p_0 \colon  fa_0=b</tex> and <tex>p_1 \colon  fa_1=b</tex>. Invoking the <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure on <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> (<ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/>), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \psi &amp; \colon  p_0 =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1    \end {aligned}  </tex>

  <p>As <tex>f</tex> is an <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">embedding</link>, the map <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  a_0 = a_1  \to  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> has an <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1} , \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>

 <p>Let <tex>\alpha   \colon  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> be the concatenation <tex>p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Therefore we may define:</p>

 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \phi &amp;: \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1}   \alpha     \end {aligned}  </tex>

 <p>To define <tex>\psi   \colon  p_0= \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1</tex> we use the counit of our <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> as we have <tex>\epsilon   \alpha   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi  = p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <tex>p_1</tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11046</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr><route>erct-002Q.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> are unique</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11047</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-002Q</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="Path object structure on sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, which follows via <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002O" href="erct-002O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11048</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr><route>erct-002T.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11049</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-002T</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases given by <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11050</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002W</addr><route>erct-002W.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002W.agda" type="external">erct-002W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11051</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-002W</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must show that each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">proposition</link>; in fact, each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">contractible</link> as <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">biinvertible maps are contractible</link>, and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11052</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr><route>erct-0027.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11053</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-0027</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  B  \to  A</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  A \to  B</tex>; if <tex>a_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex> is given by <tex>ra_0</tex>. For the rest, we use <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11054</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001N</addr><route>erct-001N.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001N.agda" type="external">erct-001N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11055</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-001N</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <tex>a,a':A</tex> with <tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> with <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, we employ the <link href="erct-0035.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0035" title="Covariant sum of a left-cloven family of path objects">covariant sum</link> of each of the <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">pointwise path object</link> structures on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</tex> over the <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object on a type">intrinsic path object</link> structure on <tex>A</tex>, constructing an identification <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> followed by a homotopy <tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</tex>. Fixing <tex>z \colon  A</tex>, we compute:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}        \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z       &amp;=        \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z        \\        &amp;=        \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z        \\        &amp;=  \chi '_z      \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>, which we may deduce from <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>